1
00:00:31,958 --> 00:00:33,708
[bell tolls]

2
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:38,541
[WOMAN]
I heard they were on vacation

3
00:00:38,625 --> 00:00:40,166
and got in a bus accident.

4
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:43,208
Just think, losing
both parents at once.

5
00:00:43,291 --> 00:00:46,833
The poor boy.
He’s an only child, isn’t he?

6
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:52,583
Yeah. Poor Subaru.
I hope he’s doing all right.

7
00:00:55,291 --> 00:00:56,958
Subaru?

8
00:00:57,041 --> 00:00:59,166
[SUBARU]
Hmm?

9
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:00,666
[HIROTO inhales]

10
00:01:00,750 --> 00:01:02,125
[HIROTO sighs sadly]

11
00:02:40,291 --> 00:02:42,333
[indistinct chattering]

12
00:02:42,416 --> 00:02:47,375
[SUBARU] Everything about this
stupid world is annoying.

13
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:50,916
Here you go. The reference
materials you wanted.

14
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,333
Thanks, I appreciate it.

15
00:02:53,416 --> 00:02:55,208
[KAWASE]
You read more books

16
00:02:55,291 --> 00:02:56,833
than anyone else I know,
Mikazuki.

17
00:02:56,916 --> 00:02:58,541
I don’t know
how you find the time.

18
00:02:58,625 --> 00:03:00,625
So, what do you think?
Are these what you need

19
00:03:00,708 --> 00:03:02,875
to find the inspiration
for your next book?

20
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:04,708
Who knows. Hope so.

21
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:07,458
-[GIRL laughing]
-[SUBARU sighs wearily]

22
00:03:07,541 --> 00:03:09,208
Listen, reading’s great,
and all.

23
00:03:09,291 --> 00:03:12,041
But you might find it
more stimulating to go outside,

24
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:14,208
get some fresh air.

25
00:03:14,291 --> 00:03:16,708
You like this place?
It’s super popular right now.

26
00:03:16,791 --> 00:03:19,083
Busy all the time. Been wanting
to come here for a while

27
00:03:19,166 --> 00:03:20,708
and our meeting
was the perfect excuse--

28
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:22,750
[SUBARU]
Hey, Kawase.

29
00:03:25,208 --> 00:03:26,416
Did you become my editor

30
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:28,708
just so you could sabotage
my productivity?

31
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:30,208
Huh?

32
00:03:30,291 --> 00:03:35,208
This café, it’s filled
with mind numbing people.

33
00:03:35,291 --> 00:03:39,250
And the inane chatter
is driving me crazy!

34
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:43,208
[chattering in background]

35
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:45,916
I’ve got to go now.
I'll see you soon.

36
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,375
[KAWASE]
Uh, okay--

37
00:03:47,458 --> 00:03:49,500
Oh. Thanks for bringing me
the books.

38
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:52,333
[chattering continues]

39
00:03:56,791 --> 00:03:59,416
[chuckling]
What have I gotten myself into?

40
00:04:02,166 --> 00:04:05,500
[KAWASE] Subaru Mikazuki,
acclaimed mystery author.

41
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:08,041
An eccentric.
Not fond of people.

42
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:10,458
His previous editor
was put on leave

43
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:12,500
for a bad case of gastritis.

44
00:04:12,583 --> 00:04:16,208
He’s sensitive.
To be handled with care.

45
00:04:16,291 --> 00:04:18,166
[SUBARU sighs]

46
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:20,458
[SUBARU] I wish I could live
on a deserted island

47
00:04:20,541 --> 00:04:22,833
and bury myself in books.

48
00:04:22,916 --> 00:04:24,875
Come to think of it,

49
00:04:24,958 --> 00:04:28,708
my parents were always trying
to get me out to see new places.

50
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:34,875
But, going out means
having to interact with people.

51
00:04:36,583 --> 00:04:39,458
[BOY] Oh, hey.
I’ve read that book before!

52
00:04:39,541 --> 00:04:41,375
Really?
Then, what was it about?

53
00:04:41,458 --> 00:04:42,750
It’s stupid.

54
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,541
The main character’s friend
is the bad guy.

55
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:46,541
-[SUBARU] Why would he-- ?
-[BOY 2] Wait, for real?

56
00:04:46,625 --> 00:04:49,708
[SUBARU] Shut your mouth!
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

57
00:04:49,791 --> 00:04:52,291
Why would someone
take the fun away from me?

58
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,750
I want to find out for myself!

59
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,416
[SUBARU] I don’t need to have
anyone around.

60
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,750
They’d only get in the way.

61
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:06,791
Mom and Dad,

62
00:05:06,875 --> 00:05:08,875
thankfully, I’ve managed
to pay the bills

63
00:05:08,958 --> 00:05:11,541
just using my imagination.

64
00:05:11,625 --> 00:05:15,375
I hope you know you don’t
have to worry about me.

65
00:05:15,458 --> 00:05:18,791
That’s another reason I’d better
come up with a new story.

66
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:22,291
Before Kawase gets any more
ideas about taking me out.

67
00:05:24,041 --> 00:05:26,041
Something bit me!

68
00:05:28,458 --> 00:05:31,208
Oh, just a cat.

69
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:34,041
I thought a zombie had leapt
out of the grave to attack me!

70
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:36,958
[SUBARU groans]

71
00:05:37,041 --> 00:05:39,333
Now that I’ve gotten
a good look,

72
00:05:39,416 --> 00:05:43,500
its mouth does remind me
a little bit of Mom’s.

73
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:47,416
Oh, come on. That’s ridiculous.
My mind’s just messing with me.

74
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:52,416
[SUBARU gasps]
I’ve got an idea

75
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:54,583
-for my next book!
-[CAT screeches]

76
00:05:56,541 --> 00:06:00,666
[SUBARU] From the shadows.
From the narrowest alleyway.

77
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:02,791
From beyond the darkness.

78
00:06:02,875 --> 00:06:05,791
I saw those fiercely
glowing eyes,

79
00:06:05,875 --> 00:06:08,791
and I was captivated!

80
00:06:08,875 --> 00:06:11,041
And from then on...

81
00:06:11,125 --> 00:06:15,083
that little cat’s had
a thirst for my blood!

82
00:06:16,458 --> 00:06:18,125
[KAWASE]
Y-ello, Koguma Publishing,

83
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:19,375
Kawase speaking.

84
00:06:19,458 --> 00:06:21,041
Hey, I got your email.

85
00:06:21,125 --> 00:06:25,083
A mystery about a cat, huh?
That sounds fascinating!

86
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:28,333
And the cat happens to be
a homicidal maniac? I'm sold.

87
00:06:28,416 --> 00:06:31,083
-[KAWASE laughing]
-Glad to hear it. Thank you.

88
00:06:31,166 --> 00:06:33,750
[KAWASE] So, this is it.
The new hit novel

89
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:35,625
all your fans
have been waiting for.

90
00:06:35,708 --> 00:06:37,166
I’m gonna need a draft
of the first chapter

91
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:39,916
by the end of the month.
Think you can manage?

92
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,291
[SUBARU] Yes. I’ve outlined
the whole plot already.

93
00:06:43,375 --> 00:06:45,083
Talk soon.

94
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:52,041
[SUBARU] It’s got the look
of murder in its eyes!

95
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:55,125
There's no doubt in my mind.
You’re a killer.

96
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:01,708
Is it signaling
to its partner in crime?

97
00:07:01,791 --> 00:07:03,791
[barking]

98
00:07:03,875 --> 00:07:07,250
[WOMAN] Stop that barking, Taro.
There’s a good boy.

99
00:07:08,416 --> 00:07:12,375
Oh. Subaru’s out?
No wonder you were barking.

100
00:07:12,458 --> 00:07:13,916
[hissing]

101
00:07:15,583 --> 00:07:18,083
[SUBARU] This must be the path
to its secret hideout.

102
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:23,166
With one spark of inspiration,
the wings of imagination unfurl!

103
00:07:25,916 --> 00:07:28,083
I can’t believe this.

104
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:30,041
I never dreamed
anything could inspire me

105
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:31,875
as much as reading books.

106
00:07:31,958 --> 00:07:34,458
Who would have thought?

107
00:07:34,541 --> 00:07:37,916
-[HIROTO] Hey, Subaru!
-[gasps]

108
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:41,333
♪

109
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:43,333
[growls]

110
00:07:43,416 --> 00:07:45,333
Hiroto.

111
00:07:45,416 --> 00:07:48,875
[HIROTO] Don’t you have anything
besides fish sausages here?

112
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:51,416
[SUBARU growls]
Criticizing my fridge?

113
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:54,083
Dammit, Hiroto, you can’t just
waltz into someone’s house

114
00:07:54,166 --> 00:07:55,875
unannounced like you
own the place!

115
00:07:55,958 --> 00:07:58,166
And you can’t raid their fridge
without permission, either!

116
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:01,083
I mean, come on, your parents
live three houses down!

117
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,625
Yeah, about that, you’re never
even going to believe

118
00:08:03,708 --> 00:08:06,666
what happened to me, Subaru.
Check this out.

119
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:08,708
Some jerk stole my wallet
while I was overseas,

120
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:10,416
and I still managed
to make it home.

121
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:11,791
But, then there was a dang fire

122
00:08:11,875 --> 00:08:13,625
on the floor
above me or something,

123
00:08:13,708 --> 00:08:15,916
and my entire apartment
got totally flooded.

124
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,708
I had no money,
I was starving,

125
00:08:17,791 --> 00:08:20,166
and when I went to my parents’
place, they weren’t home.

126
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,833
I’ve had a rough
couple days, man.

127
00:08:27,541 --> 00:08:29,708
Wait, hold on.

128
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:33,500
I got you this!

129
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:36,375
I don’t need more crap.

130
00:08:36,458 --> 00:08:38,875
Jeez, dude, sorry.
What is that?

131
00:08:41,541 --> 00:08:43,708
-A cat, what else?
-Yeah, obviously.

132
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:46,083
I’m not a moron,
but, I mean, why’s it here?

133
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:48,375
[SUBARU]
I took it in recently.

134
00:08:49,375 --> 00:08:52,000
Wait, you’re keeping it?
You, with a cat?

135
00:08:52,083 --> 00:08:54,583
The guy who doesn’t care about
anything in the world but books?

136
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:55,833
You okay?

137
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:59,875
-Will you shut up?
-Wow. Dang.

138
00:08:59,958 --> 00:09:02,083
I’m just shocked.

139
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:05,041
[SUBARU]
What are you crying about?

140
00:09:05,125 --> 00:09:08,375
I don't know,
I’m just happy for you.

141
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,791
[HIROTO] Hey, kitty.
I’ll bring you a little treat

142
00:09:11,875 --> 00:09:13,083
next time I stop by.

143
00:09:13,166 --> 00:09:14,875
-Be a good kitty for Subaru.
-[hissing]

144
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:18,708
[SUBARU] Will you just get out
of here and let me work?

145
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:21,458
[rain pouring]

146
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:35,875
[cell phone chimes, buzzes]

147
00:09:39,291 --> 00:09:41,708
[KAWASE] Ah, good,
you picked up. It’s Kawase.

148
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:43,583
Did you get those cat books
I sent over?

149
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:46,000
[SUBARU] Yeah. I did.
Just now, actually.

150
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:47,458
[KAWASE] I had no idea

151
00:09:47,541 --> 00:09:49,833
there was so much
reference material about cats.

152
00:09:49,916 --> 00:09:51,500
I’ll be sending you more later.

153
00:09:51,583 --> 00:09:53,833
Oh, fun fact, listen to this.
Did you know that cats can--

154
00:09:53,916 --> 00:09:56,250
[SUBARU] I don’t need any
useless cat facts, thanks.

155
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:57,416
[KAWASE]
Huh?

156
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,250
That’s a pet peeve of mine.

157
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:02,250
If I want information,
I can find it myself.

158
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:05,166
[KAWASE] Oh, right, of course!
Sorry about that.

159
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:07,333
[SUBARU] Just try to be more
mindful in the future.

160
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:08,666
[phone disconnects]

161
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:10,041
[groans]

162
00:10:11,666 --> 00:10:14,208
Were you just talking
to Mikazuki?

163
00:10:14,291 --> 00:10:15,791
Oh, you could tell?

164
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:18,000
He looks like such a nice kid,
but he’s got a bite.

165
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:19,708
Boy’s ruthless.

166
00:10:19,791 --> 00:10:22,625
Around here, we call writers
like that one “difficult.”

167
00:10:22,708 --> 00:10:24,041
But he’s a popular author,

168
00:10:24,125 --> 00:10:27,125
so don’t do anything
that might run him off.

169
00:10:27,208 --> 00:10:28,875
[sighs]

170
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:31,750
Oh, by the way, you might want
to keep a close eye on him

171
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:33,666
when he’s got deadlines
coming up.

172
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:34,916
[KAWASE]
Huh?

173
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,666
[SUBARU groans]

174
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:39,166
[SUBARU] That guy just won’t
leave me alone.

175
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:40,958
I want to think for myself here.

176
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:43,750
This is exactly
why I hate people.

177
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:45,166
[gasps]

178
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:47,416
♪

179
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:52,458
[gasps] A spy!

180
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:58,125
Ow! Dammit! Why is there
cat food on the floor?

181
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:05,750
-[angry meowing]
-What the hell?

182
00:11:08,625 --> 00:11:11,000
What are you even
trying to do in there?

183
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:16,875
Whoa, this must be a trap!
I see what’s going on.

184
00:11:16,958 --> 00:11:20,416
It’s a snare to throw the target
off-guard to finish the job!

185
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:23,791
This is perfect!

186
00:11:25,541 --> 00:11:27,625
You’re pretty cool,
you know that?

187
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:30,000
You don’t butt into my business
like humans do.

188
00:11:30,083 --> 00:11:32,000
And you stimulate
my imagination.

189
00:11:32,083 --> 00:11:33,791
It’s fantastic.

190
00:11:36,541 --> 00:11:39,541
This is what I get for saying
those words out loud.

191
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:43,375
I’ve had about enough
of this little stunt.

192
00:11:43,458 --> 00:11:46,166
What the hell, man?
[sighs]

193
00:11:51,833 --> 00:11:53,125
[gasps]

194
00:11:53,208 --> 00:11:56,583
♪

195
00:11:56,666 --> 00:11:59,250
"A tribute to its boss?"

196
00:12:07,041 --> 00:12:09,666
Boss.
I got somethin’ special for you.

197
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:13,208
[SUBARU] What exactly is it
you expect from me?

198
00:12:18,958 --> 00:12:22,291
I’ll just ignore it.
I’ve got a deadline coming up.

199
00:12:26,458 --> 00:12:29,166
[scratching}

200
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:30,541
[scratching continues]

201
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:32,625
[SUBARU] I don’t have time
to mess around.

202
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:36,083
[cell phone chimes, buzzes]

203
00:12:38,416 --> 00:12:41,041
[meowing]

204
00:12:41,125 --> 00:12:43,875
[cell phone chimes, buzzes]

205
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:46,833
[SUBARU]
Oh, come on!

206
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:49,541
I was told no one
would interrupt me!

207
00:12:49,625 --> 00:12:52,375
I told myself lies!

208
00:12:53,666 --> 00:12:56,833
Man. I guess cats are just
as annoying as humans.

209
00:12:56,916 --> 00:12:59,791
Nothing good ever comes
from letting them in!

210
00:13:06,666 --> 00:13:10,625
[sighs]
Okay. Finish line’s in sight.

211
00:13:10,708 --> 00:13:13,375
[rattling]

212
00:13:13,458 --> 00:13:16,541
Ah! Is something trying
to get in and kill me!

213
00:13:19,875 --> 00:13:21,875
Why’d you bring me
your whole dish?

214
00:13:21,958 --> 00:13:26,166
Come on! What is your deal, cat?
Stop interrupting my work!

215
00:13:28,416 --> 00:13:30,875
Crap. Not yet.

216
00:13:30,958 --> 00:13:34,333
I’m not finished.
My manuscript...

217
00:13:34,416 --> 00:13:36,416
It’s useless.

218
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:43,458
[cell phone chimes, buzzes]

219
00:13:43,541 --> 00:13:48,125
It’s no use. I can’t move.
I’m paralyzed.

220
00:13:58,791 --> 00:14:01,500
[KAWASE]
Mikazuki!

221
00:14:01,583 --> 00:14:04,500
Thank goodness!
I’m glad you’re awake.

222
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:07,458
[SUBARU] Kawase?
What are you doing here?

223
00:14:07,541 --> 00:14:10,458
Well, you hadn’t answered
my calls in a little while.

224
00:14:10,541 --> 00:14:12,791
So, I freaked out
and came to check on you.

225
00:14:12,875 --> 00:14:14,166
Then, when I got here,

226
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:15,666
I saw you’d passed out
in the hallway and--

227
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:18,083
And, uh, I thought you died!

228
00:14:19,958 --> 00:14:22,000
What in the hell
did you do to my window?

229
00:14:22,083 --> 00:14:24,583
I’ve already got someone
coming to replace the glass.

230
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:26,041
[groaning]

231
00:14:27,708 --> 00:14:30,541
-Hold on. My draft!
-[KAWASE] Right. The ending.

232
00:14:30,625 --> 00:14:32,750
Can we just go
with what’s written here?

233
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:34,041
[SUBARU]
Huh?

234
00:14:34,125 --> 00:14:35,375
I found your scribblings.

235
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:39,000
[SUBARU]
I don’t remember writing that.

236
00:14:39,083 --> 00:14:40,583
[KAWASE]
Anyway, someone told me

237
00:14:40,666 --> 00:14:42,666
you forget to eat and sleep
when you’re working.

238
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,833
So, I’m glad I stopped by.

239
00:14:44,916 --> 00:14:47,416
Try not to push yourself
too hard, okay?

240
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:51,125
[SUBARU] I can’t believe
I had the strength.

241
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:53,166
[coughs]

242
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:55,875
I ate cat food, didn’t I?

243
00:14:55,958 --> 00:14:58,625
Uh, Mikazuki?

244
00:14:58,708 --> 00:15:01,166
[SUBARU] Just because it
happened to be in front of me?

245
00:15:01,250 --> 00:15:02,916
Really?

246
00:15:04,291 --> 00:15:06,250
Happened to be?

247
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:09,125
It couldn’t be
a coincidence, could it?

248
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:11,166
Listen, Mikazuki.

249
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:12,958
Maybe you should go
to the doctor.

250
00:15:13,041 --> 00:15:16,416
[SUBARU] No, I’m okay now.
I just needed to rest,

251
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,583
and I hadn’t had anything
to eat in a while.

252
00:15:18,666 --> 00:15:20,666
-You sure?
-[SUBARU] Mm-hmm.

253
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,708
Hey, by the way. Um...

254
00:15:24,791 --> 00:15:27,208
Do you have any idea
what it might mean

255
00:15:27,291 --> 00:15:30,166
if someone keeps bringing their
own food to you, unsolicited?

256
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:31,750
Hold the phone, Mikazuki.

257
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,625
Are you saying
you have a girlfriend?

258
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:35,833
You’re already bragging
about her cooking, too!

259
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:37,416
[SUBARU]
What? No.

260
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:40,500
But, like...
if someone brings you food,

261
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:42,958
I think it just means that
they’re concerned about you.

262
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:46,666
Though, if you really
want to know,

263
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:49,916
why not skip all the guesswork
and just ask them yourself?

264
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,833
There are some things
you can’t figure out

265
00:15:51,916 --> 00:15:54,250
with imagination alone.

266
00:16:02,458 --> 00:16:04,791
♪

267
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:08,000
[CAT] I’ve heard legends
about wonderful humans.

268
00:16:08,083 --> 00:16:10,291
They say meeting one can alter
the course of your fate

269
00:16:10,375 --> 00:16:11,583
for the better.

270
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:13,166
If that's true,

271
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:16,750
is there a better fate
in store for me with this guy?

272
00:16:18,250 --> 00:16:21,083
He’s been doing
that thing again all day.

273
00:16:21,166 --> 00:16:23,708
I didn’t even know there were
humans who moved so little.

274
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:26,166
I followed him
because he had food,

275
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:29,000
but I had no idea
he’d be like this.

276
00:16:29,083 --> 00:16:30,958
[cell phone chimes, buzzes]

277
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:34,625
[CAT] Although, he hasn’t
done anything mean.

278
00:16:34,708 --> 00:16:37,250
He fills up my food bowl
every day.

279
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:43,958
And yet, he doesn’t eat
a single bite himself.

280
00:16:44,041 --> 00:16:47,291
[KITTEN]
Sis, I’m really hungry!

281
00:16:47,375 --> 00:16:49,958
[CAT] Doesn’t he know
if you get too hungry, you die?

282
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:51,500
He shouldn’t mess around!

283
00:16:51,583 --> 00:16:53,916
When I first met him,
he gave me food then, too,

284
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,041
but didn’t take any for himself.

285
00:16:56,125 --> 00:16:58,000
I don’t really get it,

286
00:16:58,083 --> 00:17:01,375
but I’ll never forget what
the tabby who helped me said.

287
00:17:01,458 --> 00:17:04,458
[TABBY] Always repay any favors
done for you!

288
00:17:04,541 --> 00:17:06,583
[CAT]
I live by that.

289
00:17:09,416 --> 00:17:12,291
So, I’m not going nowhere
till I pay him back.

290
00:17:12,375 --> 00:17:14,166
Since he can’t seem
to feed himself,

291
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:16,250
I’d better give him
some of my food.

292
00:17:18,791 --> 00:17:21,833
-[shrieks]
-[meows]

293
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:24,291
♪

294
00:17:26,541 --> 00:17:29,208
[CAT] He moved! The human got up
from his spot!

295
00:17:29,291 --> 00:17:31,750
I... I was just
a little surprised

296
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:33,958
because I wasn’t
expecting it, is all.

297
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:36,375
[SUBARU]
Ow! Dammit!

298
00:17:36,458 --> 00:17:39,500
[CAT] Go on,
hurry up and eat before--

299
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:42,708
♪

300
00:17:45,916 --> 00:17:47,750
[shrieks]

301
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:50,083
[CAT] What are you doing?
Are you stupid?

302
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:53,041
How dare you waste
perfectly good food like that?

303
00:17:53,125 --> 00:17:56,291
This human is bad!
It’s even worse than I thought!

304
00:17:56,375 --> 00:17:58,125
[CAT groaning]

305
00:17:58,208 --> 00:17:59,708
[SUBARU gasps]

306
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:04,541
[CAT] Unbelievable!
You’re supposed to eat it!

307
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,541
[meowing]

308
00:18:08,708 --> 00:18:10,541
For me and the rest
of my litter,

309
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:13,291
just finding enough food
to keep us alive was hard.

310
00:18:13,375 --> 00:18:15,833
Most days we barely ate at all!

311
00:18:15,916 --> 00:18:20,041
I don't know. I guess humans
take food for granted.

312
00:18:20,125 --> 00:18:23,625
I’ll repay the favor,
then split.

313
00:18:25,125 --> 00:18:27,875
♪

314
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:35,333
[scratching]

315
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,500
[groans, shrieks]

316
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:39,208
Why won’t you eat,
stupid human?

317
00:18:39,291 --> 00:18:41,041
You’re gonna eat food
and like it!

318
00:18:43,041 --> 00:18:45,625
[straining]

319
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:48,500
He can’t refuse this!

320
00:18:48,583 --> 00:18:50,916
Oh, finally decided
to come out.

321
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,666
[SUBARU] What the hell?
What is your deal?

322
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:54,916
[CAT] If you don’t eat,
you won’t be able to move!

323
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,333
That means you can’t get away
if you need to!

324
00:18:57,416 --> 00:19:00,291
Stop interrupting my work--

325
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:02,750
[thudding]

326
00:19:02,833 --> 00:19:06,041
[CAT] Hey. Human?
Are you all right?

327
00:19:11,333 --> 00:19:13,208
[CAT]
What’s up?

328
00:19:13,291 --> 00:19:16,208
Why won’t you move
or open your eyes?

329
00:19:18,541 --> 00:19:20,541
No!

330
00:19:22,958 --> 00:19:25,625
Come on.
There’s food right here!

331
00:19:25,708 --> 00:19:27,958
You just have to move
your hand a little!

332
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:31,750
You can eat it all!
I’ve had enough to tide me over!

333
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:39,791
[meowing]

334
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:45,416
[crunching]

335
00:19:47,083 --> 00:19:49,500
[CAT]
I did it! He's eating!

336
00:19:52,916 --> 00:19:53,708
Huh?

337
00:19:53,791 --> 00:19:55,375
[scribbling furiously]

338
00:19:58,208 --> 00:20:01,708
[SUBARU]
There! It’s done.

339
00:20:03,208 --> 00:20:06,666
[CAT]
Huh? What just happened?

340
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:08,458
[snoring]

341
00:20:10,958 --> 00:20:14,208
[CAT]
Is he just sleeping?

342
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:26,208
Oh, good. He feels warm.

343
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:28,416
Thank goodness.

344
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:35,708
What a strange human.
I’m glad he finally left.

345
00:20:35,791 --> 00:20:37,458
[sighs]

346
00:20:37,541 --> 00:20:39,750
[CAT] So, you’re strong enough
to walk now?

347
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,750
It’s you.
Where have you been?

348
00:20:46,458 --> 00:20:48,000
[CAT] I have
repaid your kindness

349
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:49,333
and cleared my debt.

350
00:20:49,416 --> 00:20:51,208
So, it’s time for me
to leave you now.

351
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:55,708
Just make sure you eat
enough food, okay, mister?

352
00:20:57,375 --> 00:21:01,083
[shrieks] Hey, man!
You’ve gotta keep it together!

353
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,833
Jeez.
Call yourself a person?

354
00:21:05,916 --> 00:21:08,041
I can’t leave you
alone like this!

355
00:21:09,791 --> 00:21:13,250
[SUBARU] Let’s see.
I thought I still had one left.

356
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:16,500
[gasps]

357
00:21:16,583 --> 00:21:19,500
But, like...
if someone brings you food,

358
00:21:19,583 --> 00:21:22,291
I think it just means that
they’re concerned about you.

359
00:21:24,458 --> 00:21:27,541
[SUBARU] There’s no way.
A cat wouldn’t do that.

360
00:21:27,625 --> 00:21:29,041
[objects clattering]

361
00:21:29,125 --> 00:21:30,208
[gasps]

362
00:21:30,291 --> 00:21:32,500
Found it.

363
00:21:32,583 --> 00:21:35,125
[CAT] Yes! I had that before,
but only once!

364
00:21:35,208 --> 00:21:37,666
It’s the most delicious
thing ever!

365
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:39,833
Is he gonna let me have it?

366
00:21:39,916 --> 00:21:41,875
[gasps]
What has gotten into you?

367
00:21:41,958 --> 00:21:44,625
-I don’t understand you at all.
-[CAT] Can I? I’ll be so good!

368
00:21:44,708 --> 00:21:46,291
You're hungry.

369
00:21:46,375 --> 00:21:48,666
So why have you been
giving me all your food?

370
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:50,375
Do you think...
we’re friends?

371
00:21:50,458 --> 00:21:52,458
[CAT moaning]

372
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:55,875
[shrieks]
I changed my mind.

373
00:21:55,958 --> 00:21:57,833
I’ll stay with you forever
if you want!

374
00:21:57,916 --> 00:22:00,708
Look.
If you interrupt my work again,

375
00:22:00,791 --> 00:22:02,625
I’ll run you off. You got that?

376
00:22:02,708 --> 00:22:04,958
[CAT]
Tastes so good!

377
00:22:06,833 --> 00:22:08,250
[SUBARU]
A truth.

378
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:11,000
One that can’t be found
through imagination alone.

379
00:22:11,083 --> 00:22:12,416
What’s that like?

380
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,208
[CAT]
A fateful encounter.

381
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:17,458
One that brings great changes.
What’s that like?

382
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:22,500
[SUBARU] I think, a door
to a bright new world...

383
00:22:22,583 --> 00:22:25,541
[BOTH] ...is opening...
a little at a time.

384
00:23:56,291 --> 00:23:59,083
[MAN] I brought you a little
gift to celebrate your new home!

385
00:23:59,166 --> 00:24:00,750
-Yeah, what is it?
-[MAN] A rock.

386
00:24:00,833 --> 00:24:02,708
[WOMAN] Who gives a rock
as a housewarming gift?

387
00:24:02,791 --> 00:24:04,083
[MAN] What, you mean
you don’t like it?

388
00:24:04,166 --> 00:24:05,875
Rocks make excellent gifts!

